However, based on the available data and the system constraints, I need to provide my analysis with what\'s available.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_metric_keys": ["error_ratio", "rrt_max", "rrt", "client_error_ratio", "server_error_ratio"],\n  "affected_components": ["cartservice-0", "cartservice-1", "cartservice-2", "frontend-0", "frontend-1", "frontend-2", "shippingservice-0", "shippingservice-1", "shippingservice-2", "redis-cart-0"],\n  "metric_summary": "Multiple services experiencing high error ratios (20-50%) and severe latency degradation during fault window. cartservice, frontend, shippingservice, and redis-cart-0 all show significant error rate spikes and rrt_max increases from thousands to millions of microseconds.",\n  "time_series_analysis": {\n    "metric_name": "error_ratio",\n    "pattern": "sudden_spike",\n    "critical_timestamps": ["2025-06-05T18:10:05Z"],\n    "value_change": "0.0 → 20-50%"\n  },\n  "contradictions": [],\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_logs",\n    "reason": "Infrastructure metrics unavailable for this date. Need to verify if redis-cart-0 failure caused cascading issues to dependent services like cartservice",\n    "suggested_metrics": [],\n    "suggested_log_keywords": ["redis", "connection refused", "timeout", "cartservice"]\n  }\n}\n```'}
